# Top-level deps for the persona-sandbox image (spec 25 T07 / D-25-1 / R-25-2;
# originally spec 12 T06 / R-12-3).
#
# Compile into a hash-verified ``requirements.txt`` via, *run under the image's
# own interpreter* (python:3.11-slim-bookworm) so the resolved markers match the
# runtime — see README "Regenerating the lock":
#
#   piptools compile --generate-hashes --output-file=requirements.txt requirements.in
#
# Versions are the D-25-1 / R-25-2 pinned snapshot for mid-2026 (the spec-12
# core eight carry forward their D-12-2 pins). Re-resolve at build time and
# commit the resulting requirements.txt; the runtime refuses any wheel whose
# sha256 does not match (PyPA hash-mode). ``--require-hashes`` also forbids
# unpinned deps, forcing a fully resolved lock — and neutralises the active
# ``sympy-dev`` typosquat miner campaign ONLY when regen always resolves these
# canonical PyPI names against canonical PyPI (R-25-2 OQ-R2-5).

# --- numerics + scientific computing (Spec 17) ---
numpy==2.1.3
scipy==1.14.1
pandas==2.2.3
sympy==1.13.3
statsmodels==0.14.4
scikit-learn==1.5.2
networkx==3.4.2

